<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>
<p>Large <rs type="material">white marble</rs> <rs type="objectType">block</rs> without moulding <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">1.90</measure>  × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.87</measure>  × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.42</measure> from a built tomb.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="text">
<head>Description of Text</head>
<p> <rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> on the exposed face in different hands; at least one text (a), began on a block above. Beside this, text b, to the right, is  perhaps a casual graffito.  To the left of a and b is inscribed text c, in an area which is damaged at the left side.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Letters</head>
<p>a: <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.08</measure> b: cursive, <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre" precision="circa">0.05</measure>; ll. 1-2, <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.025</measure>, l.3, <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.02</measure>.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p> a. <date notBefore="-0033" notAfter="0033" exact="none" cert="low">perhaps late first century B.C. or early Julio-Claudian</date>; b. undateable; c. <date notAfter="0068" notBefore="-0027" exact="none" cert="low">perhaps Julio-Claudian</date> (<rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>).</p>
</div>
<div type="edition" lang="grc">
<head lang="en">Edition</head>
<div type="textpart_fragment" n="a"><ab>  <lb n="0"/><gap reason="lost" extent="3" unit="character"/>  <lb n="1"/> <w lemma="χαίρω">χαῖρε</w></ab></div><div type="textpart_fragment" n="b"><ab>   <lb n="1"/> <orig n="unresolved">α<unclear reason="damage">ιι</unclear></orig> <space extent="3" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>  </ab></div><div type="textpart_fragment" n="c"><ab>   <lb n="1"/><persName type="aphrodisian"><name reg="Μηνόδοτος"><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">Μη</supplied>νόδοτος</name></persName>  <lb n="2"/><persName type="aphrodisian"><name reg="Ἀλέξανδρος"><supplied reason="lost">Ἀ</supplied><unclear reason="damage">λ</unclear>εξάνδρου</name></persName>  <lb n="3"/><w><gap reason="lost" extent="1" unit="character"/>ιος</w> <w lemma="χαίρω">χαῖρε</w> </ab></div>
</div>

<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p> a: <gap extent="unknown" reason="lost" unit="character"/> farewell. c: Menodotos, son of Alexandros <gap extent="unknown" reason="lost" unit="character"/> farewell</p>
</div>
<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>I take the first word in l. 3 to be probably a second name for ?Menodotos; its first letter is lost, the second has a horizontal on the base line, but is almost certainly not Δ: e.g. Ἀσιος vel. sim. The traces do not accord with any of the epithets which commonly appear in this position in epitaphs - e.g. ἀώρος, χρῆστος; and in any case these would normally be in the vocative.</p>
</div>
